_chrysocolla_ver01/data/sn89070012/00517019549/1949060201/1085.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn89070012/1949-06-02/ed-1/?sp=2"], "batch": ["az_chrysocolla_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/arizona/", "2/united states/arizona/cochise/", "3/united states/arizona/cochise/bisbee/"], "contributor": ["arizona state library, archives and public records; phoenix, az"], "date": "1949-06-02", "dates": ["1949-06-02"], "description": ["PAGE TWO V6Q NOT SO Dum EL DUMBO Old Si Whiffc ee who comes into town a couple cf mes a year from his home out in he Cherry cows was in the fTst of the week to stock up on eatin tobacker and other necessities of life and to get the news if any He has no radio no neighbors and never reads the newspapers and so nat urally he gets quite a fur piece behind on the news Last time he was in town was a week or so before the election last fall didnt have no curiosity about how the election came out for like he says It dont make no difference whos elected Theyre all alike them politicians and it dont make no never mind to me who the president is They dont none of em ever do any thing for me But when he heard about the mines laying off men and heard the squawks of the business men about the depression or recession he knda peked up and said Well President Truman told you last fall what would happen when you elected ewey He said the Republicans would stick a knife in your back"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2024-02-25T01:00:53.021Z", "group": ["ndnp/az", "arizona-state-university-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn89070012/1949-06-02/ed-1/?sp=2", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:az:batch_az_chrysocolla_ver01:data:sn89070012:00517019549:1949060201:1085/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=404&w=269", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:az:batch_az_chrysocolla_v